cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SY, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 

1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with a cellular network system and proposes a user scheduling algorithm and power optimization strategy to improve network utility. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses interference decoding and cancellation techniques to mitigate self-interference and uplink-to-downlink interference, which are related to information theory. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper considers indoor scenarios, which are often associated with multimedia applications, and aims to improve cell throughput, which is relevant to multimedia quality of service. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a strategy that utilizes different transmission modes (full-duplex, half-duplex, and SIC) based on their impact on network utility, which can be seen as a control problem. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - Although not the main focus of the paper, the proposed strategy may have implications for security and privacy in cellular networks, as interference cancellation can potentially reveal sensitive information.
